# FastAPI Backend Service — Walkthrough

## Summary

Created a complete **FastAPI backend** under `backend/` with 12 files — JWT-authenticated REST API, async PostgreSQL, structured JSON logging, and a production-ready Dockerfile.

## File Structure

```
backend/
├── .env.example              ← all env vars (never committed)
├── requirements.txt           ← pinned Python deps
├── Dockerfile                 ← multi-stage build with tesseract + opencv
└── app/
    ├── main.py                ← FastAPI app, lifespan, CORS, health check
    ├── config.py              ← pydantic-settings from .env
    ├── database.py            ← asyncpg pool (connect/disconnect/check)
    ├── models/
    │   └── schemas.py         ← Pydantic request/response models
    ├── routers/
    │   ├── auth.py            ← JWT middleware + profile endpoints
    │   ├── analyses.py        ← CRUD + metrics + suggestions
    │   └── reports.py         ← CRUD with ownership checks
    ├── services/
    │   └── __init__.py        ← business logic placeholder
    └── utils/
        └── logging.py         ← structured JSON logging
```

## API Endpoints

All routes under **`/api/v1`**:

| Method | Path | Auth | Description |
|--------|------|------|-------------|
| `GET` | `/health` | ✗ | DB + Tesseract health check |
| `GET` | `/auth/me` | ✓ | Get current user's profile |
| `PATCH` | `/auth/me` | ✓ | Update profile fields |
| `GET` | `/analyses/` | ✓ | List user's analyses |
| `POST` | `/analyses/` | ✓ | Create new analysis |
| `GET` | `/analyses/{id}` | ✓ | Get single analysis |
| `DELETE` | `/analyses/{id}` | ✓ | Delete analysis (cascades) |
| `GET` | `/analyses/{id}/metrics` | ✓ | Get detailed metrics |
| `GET` | `/analyses/{id}/suggestions` | ✓ | Get improvement suggestions |
| `GET` | `/reports/` | ✓ | List user's reports |
| `POST` | `/reports/` | ✓ | Create report (requires completed analysis) |
| `GET` | `/reports/{id}` | ✓ | Get single report |
| `DELETE` | `/reports/{id}` | ✓ | Delete report |

## JWT Authentication Flow

1. Client sends `Authorization: Bearer <supabase-jwt>` header
2. [get_current_user](file:///f:/C%20drive%20data/squintscale/backend/app/routers/auth.py#32-57) dependency decodes JWT with `SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET` (HS256)
3. Validates `aud == "authenticated"` and extracts `sub` (user UUID)
4. Returns 401 if invalid/expired

