## How to Run

### Docker
```bash
cd backend
cp .env.example .env   # fill in real values
docker build -t squintscale-backend .
docker run -p 8080:8080 --env-file .env squintscale-backend
```

### Local (dev)
```bash
cd backend
pip install -r requirements.txt
cp .env.example .env   # fill in real values
uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8080
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The backend expects Supabase Postgres to be running. Start the Supabase Docker stack first (`cd supabase && docker compose up -d`), then launch the backend.
